title: Laggy after being great for years
text: Became super laggy in early 2024 after many years of functioning great. This is on an iPhone 14 Pro (updated and non-updated, still laggy). Such a shame. Another huge complaint is the news cards refresh seconds after opening the app, so sometimes I will see something I am interested in and then it refreshes before I have a chance to click on it and then I‚Äôll have to memorize the title quickly and search google for the article. I really hope they fix these two issues and I‚Äôll be happy to update my review to 5 stars.

title: Google- The Internet Scammer of Businesses
text:
Businesses are starting to realize that Google scams them by suggesting ads that the consumer doesn‚Äôt need or isn‚Äôt interested in.

In my example, Google regularly scams pet services (vets) and pet food, and Chewy out of money knowing that I don‚Äôt have a dog, and haven‚Äôt had since I was 14??

Google also scams out dental implants services while my teeth are fine (regular checkups and ckeanings), unless Google sends out some of its goons to beat me up. Then I may need dental implants and maybe a dog for protection.

Co-Pilot is not that great, but Google‚Äôs search engine is just too corrupt, since they seem to return results for those that will pay the most instead of returning real answers. title: Xfinity app is terrible
text:
Super easy to use if you‚Äôre going to send the money or add more things that cost money. Terrible to use if you‚Äôre just trying to find out why you can‚Äôt access things that you already pay for. Or why there are parental controls on your TV even though you‚Äôre in your 60s, and you‚Äôve never put parental controls on your TV. Or why you can‚Äôt stream in the app itself. The responses are circular click here for more information and then send you back to the page where you asked the question in the first place.
This week rather than spending my time trying to get the app to work I‚Äôm going to spend my time, figuring out how to best cut the cord and leave Xfinity altogether. Bad app is the only way to access customer service. Sigh.
